Req. ID: 299483 
In this job function, it is important for you to work closely with category supplier managers, supply chain, and business units (BUs) to develop and execute a holistic strategy and be part of a global team. You will also understand the market position of each supplier for specific materials, assessing the financial stability of suppliers, executing supply assurance, purchasing material with the balance of inventory level, and provide input and recommendations to Micron Management. 
This position also requires that you serve as the primary point of contact for resolving critical supplier demand/supply issues and oversee internal communication related to partners. 
Responsibilities include, but not limited to: 
Implement recommended actions to achieve targets for material fulfillment, on-time delivery, inventory management/turns, safety stock and replenishment points 
Implement inventory specific savings levers such as vendor stocking, supplier managed, or consignment programs 
Execute the implementation of inventory strategies and compliance and participate in the resolution of any supply constraints or issues 
Deliver supplier evaluation /quarterly business review (QBR) scorecard metric targets to Category Team 
Monitor and adjust global inventory compliance to regulatory and policy requirements 
Ensure stakeholder requirements are met through early engagement and expertise through the value chain 
Maintain positive relationships with partners 
Drive and sustain effective communication with internal and external partners 
Drive for continuous process/system improvement/automation/optimization 
Collaborate internally to develop key performance measures/metrics and monitor category and supplier performance against these expectations to ensure continuous performance improvement 
Perform data analysis that can be leveraged in negotiation and sourcing strategy 
Qualifications & Experience: 
Minimum 2 yearsâ€™ experience in any field: Supply Management, Material Analysis/Management 
Ability to quickly gather and analyze data and grasp customer requirements under time constraints in a changing environment 
Extremely strong analytical skills 
A high level of accuracy and attention to detail 
Communication/Presentation skills necessary to professionally represent Micron to the suppliers 
Problem solving and project management skills 
Ability to work independently or with a cross-functional team 
Proficiency in MS Outlook, Excel, PowerPoint, MS Teams. SAP experience preferred 
Experience/knowledge with silicon supply management is preferred 
Education: 
Bachelorâ€™s degree at minimum in Engineering, Supply Chain, Industrial engineering or related field 
